Quote:  FAMILY ALLOWANCES (Title) New Zealand was one of the first, if not the first, country to adopt the principle embodied in the Family Allowances Act, 1926, of the State bearing to some extent the responsibility for the well-being of the families of those who were in poorer circumstances.] Formerly a payment made by the State to a parent for the support of a child or children; ?now incorporated in the Domestic Purposes Benefit. Also called family allowance.
